==English==

===Noun===

'''[[occlude]]d front'''

# ([[Meteorology]]). An occluded front occurs when a [[cold front]] overtakes a [[warm front]] at the surface and a temperature contrast exists between the [[advancing]] and [[retreating]] cold air masses.

